# Deploy and SEO compliance (this repo)

## Canonical site URL

- **`NEXT_PUBLIC_SITE_URL`** in Vercel (Production): exactly **one** origin, **no trailing slash** (e.g. `https://anishsukhramani.com`). This drives [`src/lib/env.ts`](src/lib/env.ts) → metadata, sitemap, robots, and post canonicals.
- In **Vercel → Domains**, redirect the **non-primary** host (apex vs `www`) with **301** to that same origin so crawlers never see two live sites.

## Routes and sitemap

- When you add or remove **indexable** top-level pages, update the static path list in [`src/app/sitemap.ts`](src/app/sitemap.ts) so it stays in sync with [`src/app/`](src/app/).

## Lighthouse CI (`lighthouserc.json`)

- URLs under `ci.collect.url` are audited against `next start`. If you **remove or rename** a post whose `/blog/...` URL is listed there (e.g. `seo-systems-for-editorial-sites`), **update [`lighthouserc.json`](lighthouserc.json)** or the workflow will fail on a 404.
- After large performance, accessibility, or metadata changes, run locally: `npm run build && npm run lhci` (Chrome required). Tightening category `minScore` values increases CI flakiness, especially on **mobile** performance.

## Optional GitHub

- To **block merges** when Lighthouse fails: branch protection on `main` → require the status check for the **Lighthouse audit** job (see comments in [`.github/workflows/lighthouse.yml`](.github/workflows/lighthouse.yml)).
